The tool chain sends a 500 KByte email to each person as notification (normal average email size: 80-120 KBytes). This clogs end-user mailboxes quickly (most mailboxes have a limit of 50 to 100 MB, i.e. a capacity for 100-200 of such application-generated email). End users will have to permanently delete these messages, as upon reaching their mailbox quota, they will be unable to send email. Also, there are backend systems such as Journaling and Virtually Unlimited Mailbox, which need to store these irrelevant emails for many years, even if deleted. What a waste of processing and storage capacity. 

Could you please investigate to minimize that notifications?

