In the Release Notes of our EAP versions, we had a note as in the below:
{quote}
Please note, in this release, choosing *Blank Project, Bug Tracking, Software Development* or *Project Management* in the dialog will create the default JIRA project. However, we are in the process of developing pre-configured project templates for project types. We are considering custom workflows, sample data, preset issue types, default fields, etc, for these templates.
{quote}
This status has not yet changed as this dialog still does not make any difference while creating a project in JIRA. In our [Defining a Project - Adding a Project|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Defining+a+Project#DefiningaProject-Addingaproject] we have a note as the above, but this was removed from the [JIRA 6.0 Release Notes|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/JIRA+6.0+Release+Notes].

This will likely cause friction in support as the majority of the JIRA users will not read the [Defining a Project|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Defining+a+Project#DefiningaProject-Addingaproject] documentation when creating a project, so they will expect its behaviour to be different. In order to reduce friction and confusion for our customers, we should add this same note to the current [JIRA 6.0 Release Notes|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/JIRA+6.0+Release+Notes].

